snippet.textDisplay:
I don't think I'll ever understand the praise this album gets. Devil In A New Dress is the one great song on here. Power and a couple others are good, and the rest is pretty embarrassing honestly. I've seen so many 10/10 and "album of the decade" reviews for this though and I'd just like someone to explain to me how?

My theory is that people just parrot what others say for this in fear of being labeled as uncool or uninformed.

Kanye proclaims himself a genius, his fans believe it because he does faux artsy shit like Runaway and follow suit, and eventually perception becomes reality.

If any other rapper made this album it'd be forgotten immediately. It's lauded for the same reason his Walmart Dad shoes sell for hundreds of dollars and are considered high fashion. His influence far outweighs his actual art, but it doesn't matter because his influence creates the narratives that surround him.
